                                  IParentEntitySupplier parentEntitySupplier)
        Constructs a new keyed node generator.
        Parameters:
        sortOrder - Sort order for generated nodes.
        parent - Used to get or create a parent node for generated nodes; if null is passed, this keyed node generator has no parent.
        parentEntitySupplier - Used to supply an entity for the parent; if null is passed, SelfParentEntitySupplier will be used instead.

      • getOrCreateNode

        public AbstractOrderedDiffTreeNode getOrCreateNode(KeyableBean entity,
                                                   java.util.Date effDate,
                                                   java.util.Map<DiffTreeNodeKey,AbstractOrderedDiffTreeNode> nodeMap)
        Description copied from interface: IKeyedNodeGenerator
        Returns the node from the given nodeMap by using a key created from the given entity and effDate. If no such node exists, inserts and returns a new node with the expected key.
        Specified by:
        getOrCreateNode in interface IKeyedNodeGenerator
        Parameters:
        entity - Entity for which to retrieve / create a node (used as part of key creation).
        effDate - Date for which to retrieve / create a node (used as part of key creation).
        nodeMap - Map of nodes.
        Returns:
        An existing or newly created node for the passed entity.
        See Also:
        IKeyedNodeGenerator.getUniqueKey(KeyableBean, Date)

      • createNode

        protected abstract AbstractOrderedDiffTreeNode createNode(KeyableBean entity,
                                                          java.util.Date effDate)
        Creates a new node from scratch. Called from getOrCreateNode(KeyableBean, Date, Map) when no matching node is found in the node map.
        Parameters:
        entity - KeyableBean for which to create a new node.
        effDate - Date for which to create a new node.
        Returns:

      • getOrCreateNodeWithCreator

        protected final AbstractOrderedDiffTreeNode getOrCreateNodeWithCreator(KeyableBean entity,
                                                                       java.util.Date effDate,
                                                                       java.util.Map<DiffTreeNodeKey,AbstractOrderedDiffTreeNode> nodeMap,
                                                                       IValueCreator<AbstractOrderedDiffTreeNode> creator)
        Calls getUniqueKey(KeyableBean, Date to generate a key for the passed entity, then calls getOrCreate(DiffTreeNodeKey, Map, IValueCreator) with the generated key, the passed nodeMap, and a creator that calls through to createNodeWithCreator(KeyableBean, Date, Map, IValueCreator) with the passed entity, creator, and nodeMap.
        Parameters:
        entity - KeyableBean for which to generate a key / node (used as part of key creation).
        effDate - Date for which to generate a key / node (used as part of key creation).
        nodeMap - Map of nodes from which to lookup existing nodes.
        creator - Used to create the node if no existing one can be found.
        Returns:
        An existing node for the entity if one exists, otherwise a freshly created node.

        Parameters:
        key - The key to use for lookup.

        creator - IValueCreator which will be invoked to create the new value if it doesn't exist in the map.
